Passes the bearer\'s held item to an ally when the ally uses up its item.','Passes the bearer\'s held item to an ally when the ally uses up its item.',6,0,NULL),(181,'tough-claws','Tough Claws','Strengthens moves that make contact to 1.33× their power.','Strengthens moves that make contact to 1.33× their power.',6,0,NULL),(182,'pixilate','Pixilate','Turns the bearer\'s Normal moves into Fairy moves and strengthens them to 1.3× their power.','Turns the bearer\'s Normal-type moves into Fairy moves. Moves changed by this ability have 1.3× their power.',6,0,NULL),(183,'gooey','Gooey','Lowers attacking Pokémon\'s Speed by one stage on contact.','Lowers attacking Pokémon\'s Speed by one stage on contact.',6,0,NULL),(184,'aerilate','Aerilate','Turns the bearer\'s Normal moves into Flying moves and strengthens them to 1.3× their power.','Turns the bearer\'s Normal-type moves into Flying-type moves. Moves changed by this ability have 1.3× their power.',6,0,NULL),(185,'parental-bond','Parental Bond','Lets the bearer hit twice with damaging moves. The second hit has half power.','Lets the bearer hit twice with damaging moves. The second hit has half power.',6,0,NULL),(186,'dark-aura','Dark Aura','Strengthens Dark moves to 1.33× their power for all friendly and opposing Pokémon.','Strengthens Dark moves for all friendly and opposing Pokémon.',6,0,NULL),(187,'fairy-aura','Fairy Aura','Strengthens Fairy moves to 1.33× their power for all friendly and opposing Pokémon.','Strengthens Fairy moves for all friendly and opposing Pokémon.',6,0,NULL),(188,'aura-break','Aura Break','Makes Dark Aura and Fairy Aura weaken moves of their respective types.','While this Pokémon is on the field, Dark Aura and Fairy Aura weaken moves of their respective types to 2/3 their power, rather than strengthening them.',6,0,NULL),(189,'primordial-sea','Primordial Sea','Creates heavy rain, which has all the properties of Rain Dance, cannot be replaced, and causes damaging Fire moves to fail.','When this Pokémon enters battle or gains this ability, the weather becomes heavy rain. Heavy rain has all the properties of Rain Dance and also causes damaging Fire moves to fail. Heavy rain ends when this Pokémon leaves battle or loses this ability, or when this ability is nullified. The weather cannot otherwise be changed except by the effects of Delta Stream and Desolate Land. Air Lock and Cloud Nine will prevent the effects of heavy rain, including allowing Fire moves to work, but will not allow the weather to be changed.',6,0,NULL),(190,'desolate-land','Desolate Land','Creates extremely harsh sunlight, which has all the properties of Sunny Day, cannot be replaced, and causes damaging Water moves to fail.','When this Pokémon enters battle or gains this ability, the weather becomes extremely harsh sunlight. Extremely harsh sunlight has all the properties of Sunny Day and also causes damaging Water moves to fail. Extremely harsh sunlight ends when this Pokémon leaves battle or loses this ability, or when this ability is nullified. The weather cannot otherwise be changed except by the effects of Delta Stream and Primordial Sea. Air Lock and Cloud Nine will prevent the effects of extremely harsh sunlight, including allowing Water moves to work, but will not allow the weather to be changed.',6,0,NULL),(191,'delta-stream','Delta Stream','Creates a mysterious air current, which cannot be replaced and causes moves to never be super effective against Flying Pokémon.','When this Pokémon enters battle or gains this ability, the weather becomes a mysterious air current. A mysterious air current causes moves to not be super effective against Flying; they do neutral damage instead. Anticipation and Stealth Rock are not affected. The mysterious air current ends when this Pokémon leaves battle or loses this ability, or when this ability is nullified. The weather cannot otherwise be changed except by the effects of Desolate Land and Primordial Sea. Air Lock and Cloud Nine will prevent the effect of a mysterious air current, but will not allow the weather to be changed.',6,0,NULL),(192,'stamina','Stamina','Raises this Pokémon\'s Defense by one stage when it takes damage from a move.','Raises this Pokémon\'s Defense by one stage when it takes damage from a move.',7,0,NULL),(193,'wimp-out','Wimp Out','This Pokémon automatically switches out when its HP drops below half.','After this Pokémon is hit by a move, if that move caused this Pokémon\'s HP to drop below half, it switches out.',7,0,NULL),(194,'emergency-exit','Emergency Exit','This Pokémon automatically switches out when its HP drops below half.','After this Pokémon is hit by a move, if that move caused this Pokémon\'s HP to drop below half, it switches out.',7,0,NULL),(195,'water-compaction','Water Compaction','Raises this Pokémon\'s Defense by two stages when it\'s hit by a Water move.','Raises this Pokémon\'s Defense by two stages when it\'s hit by a Water move.',7,0,NULL),(196,'merciless','Merciless','This Pokémon\'s moves critical hit against poisoned targets.','This Pokémon\'s moves critical hit against poisoned targets.',7,0,NULL),(197,'shields-down','Shields Down','Transforms this Minior between Core Form and Meteor Form. Prevents major status ailments and drowsiness while in Meteor Form.','When this Pokémon enters battle and at the end of each turn, if its HP is 50% or above, it changes into Meteor Form; otherwise, it changes into Core Form. In Meteor Form, it cannot be given a major status ailment (though existing ones are not cured), cannot become drowsy from Yawn, and cannot use Rest (which will simply fail). This ability cannot be copied, replaced, or nullified. This ability only takes effect for Minior.',7,0,NULL),(198,'stakeout','Stakeout','This Pokémon\'s moves have double power against Pokémon that switched in this turn.','This Pokémon\'s moves have double power against Pokémon that switched in this turn.',7,0,NULL),(199,'water-bubble','Water Bubble','Halves damage from Fire moves, doubles damage of Water moves, and prevents burns.','When this Pokémon is hit by a Fire move, the damage is halved. When this Pokémon uses a Water move, the power is doubled. This Pokémon cannot be burned, and if it becomes burned, the burn is immediately cured.',7,0,NULL),(200,'steelworker','Steelworker','This Pokémon\'s Steel moves have 1.5× power.','This Pokémon\'s Steel moves have 1.5× power.',7,0,NULL),(201,'berserk','Berserk','Raises this Pokémon\'s Special Attack by one stage every time its HP drops below half.','Whenever this Pokémon takes damage from a move that causes its HP to drop below 50%, its Special Attack rises by one stage.',7,0,NULL),(202,'slush-rush','Slush Rush','During Hail, this Pokémon has double Speed.','During Hail, this Pokémon has double Speed.',7,0,NULL),(203,'long-reach','Long Reach','This Pokémon\'s moves do not make contact.','A move used by this Pokémon will not make contact.',7,0,NULL),(204,'liquid-voice','Liquid Voice','Sound-based moves become Water-type.','When this Pokémon uses a move that is sound-based, that move\'s type is Water.',7,0,NULL),(205,'triage','Triage','This Pokémon\'s healing moves have their priority increased by 3.','This Pokémon\'s healing moves have their priority increased by 3.',7,0,NULL),(206,'galvanize','Galvanize','This Pokémon\'s Normal moves are Electric and have their power increased to 1.2×.','When this Pokémon uses a Normal moves, that move is Electric its power is 1.2×.',7,0,NULL),(207,'surge-surfer','Surge Surfer','Doubles this Pokémon\'s Speed on Electric Terrain.','Doubles this Pokémon\'s Speed on Electric Terrain.',7,0,NULL),(208,'schooling','Schooling','Wishiwashi becomes Schooling Form when its HP is 25% or higher.','If this Pokémon is a Wishiwashi and level 20 or above, then when it enters battle and at the start of each turn, it becomes Schooling Form if its HP is 25% or higher and Solo Form otherwise. This ability cannot be replaced, copied, or nullified.',7,0,NULL),(209,'disguise','Disguise','Prevents the first instance of battle damage.','If this Pokémon is in its Disguised Form and takes damage from a move, it switches to its Busted Form and the damage is prevented. Other effects are not prevented. This ability cannot be copied or replaced. This ability only takes effect for Mimikyu.',7,0,NULL),(210,'battle-bond','Battle Bond','Transforms this Pokémon into Ash-Greninja after fainting an opponent. Water Shuriken\'s power is 20 and always hits three times.','Transforms this Pokémon into Ash-Greninja after fainting an opponent. Water Shuriken\'s power is 20 and always hits three times. This ability cannot be copied or replaced. This ability only takes effect for Greninja.',7,0,NULL),(211,'power-construct','Power Construct','Transforms 10% or 50% Zygarde into Complete Forme when its HP is below 50%.','Transforms 10% or 50% Zygarde into Complete Forme when its HP is below 50%. This ability cannot be copied or replaced. This ability only takes effect for Zygarde.',7,0,NULL),(212,'corrosion','Corrosion','This Pokémon can inflict poison on Poison and Steel Pokémon.','This Pokémon\'s moves and item ignore the usual immunity of Poison and Steel Pokémon when attempting to inflict poison.',7,0,NULL),(213,'comatose','Comatose','This Pokémon always acts as though it were Asleep.','This Pokémon always acts as though it were Asleep. It cannot be given another status ailment; it\'s unaffected by Yawn; it can use Sleep Talk; and so on.',7,0,NULL),(214,'queenly-majesty','Queenly Majesty','Opposing Pokémon cannot use priority attacks.','When an opposing Pokémon attempts to use a move that targets this Pokémon or an ally, and that move has priority, it will fail.',7,0,NULL),(215,'innards-out','Innards Out','When this Pokémon faints from an opponent\'s move, that opponent takes damage equal to the HP this Pokémon had remaining.','When this Pokémon faints from an opponent\'s move, that opponent takes damage equal to the HP this Pokémon had remaining.',7,0,NULL),(216,'d