nes',0,NULL,'Teaches Waterfall to a compatible Pokémon. (HS: Whirlpool DPP: Defog Gen III & II & I: Flash)','Teaches Defog to a compatible Pokémon.',0,1,NULL),(402,'hm06','HM06','all-machines',0,NULL,'Teaches Dive to a compatible Pokémon. (Gen IV & III: Rock Smash Gen II: Whirlpool)','Teaches Rock Smash to a compatible Pokémon.',0,1,NULL),(403,'hm07','HM07','all-machines',0,NULL,'Teaches a move to a compatible Pokémon. (Gen IV & III & II: Waterfall)','Teaches Waterfall to a compatible Pokémon.',0,1,NULL),(404,'hm08','HM08','all-machines',0,NULL,'Teaches a move to a compatible Pokémon. (Gen IV: Rock Climb Gen III: Dive)','Teaches Rock Climb to a compatible Pokémon.',0,1,NULL),(405,'explorer-kit','Explorer Kit','gameplay',0,NULL,'Allows visiting the Underground.','Sends the trainer to the Underground. Only usable outside.',0,1,NULL),(406,'loot-sack','Loot Sack','unused',0,NULL,'Carries coal mine loot.','Unused.',0,1,NULL),(407,'rule-book','Rule Book','unused',0,NULL,'List of battle types and their rules.','Unused.',0,1,NULL),(408,'poke-radar','Poké Radar','gameplay',0,NULL,'Use to track down rare or shiny Pokémon. 50 steps to recharge.','Designates several nearby patches of grass as containing Pokémon, some of which may be special radar-only Pokémon. Successive uses in a certain way create chains of encounters with the same species; longer chains increase the chance that a shiny Pokémon of that species will appear.',0,1,NULL),(409,'point-card','Point Card','gameplay',0,NULL,'Keeps count of Battle Points earned.','Tracks Battle Points.',0,1,NULL),(410,'journal','Journal','gameplay',0,NULL,'Records prior significant activities the player took.','Records some of the trainer’s activities for the day.',0,1,NULL),(411,'seal-case','Seal Case','gameplay',0,NULL,'Stores Seals that can be applied to Poké Ball capsules.','Contains Seals used for decorating Pokéballs.',0,1,NULL),(412,'fashion-case','Fashion Case','gameplay',0,NULL,'Holds Pokémon Accessories for use in Contests.','Contains Pokémon Accessories.',0,1,NULL),(413,'seal-bag','Seal Bag','unused',0,NULL,'Holds ten Seals for Poké Balls.','Unused.',0,1,NULL),(414,'pal-pad','Pal Pad','gameplay',0,NULL,'Use to record Friend Codes and check your own.','Contains friend codes for up to 32 other players, as well as their sprite, gender, and basic statistics for those that have been seen on WFC.',0,1,NULL),(415,'works-key','Works Key','plot-advancement',0,NULL,'Grants access to Valley Windworks.','Opens the front door of the Valley Windworks. Reusable.',0,1,NULL),(416,'old-charm','Old Charm','plot-advancement',0,NULL,'Trade to Cynthia’s grandmother in Celestic Town for HM04 (Surf).','Given to Cynthia’s grandmother to get the Surf HM.',0,1,NULL),(417,'galactic-key','Galactic Key','plot-advancement',0,NULL,'Grants access to Galactic HQ in Veilstone City.','Grants access to Galactic HQ in Veilstone City.',0,1,NULL),(418,'red-chain','Red Chain','unused',0,NULL,'Used to bind Palkia and Dialga.','Unused.',0,1,NULL),(419,'town-map','Town Map','gameplay',0,NULL,'Use to see the overworld map.','Displays a map of the region including the trainer’s position, location names, visited towns, gym locations, and where the trainer has been walking recently.',0,1,NULL),(420,'vs-seeker','Vs. Seeker','gameplay',0,NULL,'Allows rebattling of on-screen trainers. 100 steps to recharge.','Reveals trainers who want a rematch, by showing !! over their heads. Each use drains the battery; requires 100 steps to charge.',0,1,NULL),(421,'coin-case','Coin Case','gameplay',0,NULL,'Holds coins for the Game Corner.','Contains the Coins used by the Game Corner, to a maximum of 50,000.',0,1,NULL),(422,'old-rod','Old Rod','gameplay',0,NULL,'Used to catch Pokémon in bodies of water.','Used to find Pokémon on the Old Rod list for an area, which are generally Magikarp or similar.',0,1,NULL),(423,'good-rod','Good Rod','gameplay',0,NULL,'Used to catch Pokémon in bodies of water.','Used to find Pokémon on the Good Rod list for an area, which are generally mediocre.',0,1,NULL),(424,'super-rod','Super Rod','gameplay',0,NULL,'Used to catch Pokémon in bodies of water.','Used to find Pokémon on the Super Rod list for an area, which are generally the best available there.',0,1,NULL),(425,'sprayduck','Sprayduck','gameplay',0,NULL,'Used to water berries.','Waters Berry plants.',0,1,NULL),(426,'poffin-case','Poffin Case','gameplay',0,NULL,'Holds Poffins.','Contains up to 100 Poffins.',0,1,NULL),(427,'bicycle','Bicycle','gameplay',0,NULL,'Use for fast transit.','Increases movement speed outside or in caves. In high gear, allows the trainer to hop over some rocks and ascend muddy slopes.',0,1,NULL),(428,'suite-key','Suite Key','event-items',0,NULL,'Opens a locked building in the Lakeside Resort.','Opens the locked building in the lakeside resort.',0,1,NULL),(429,'oaks-letter','Oak’s Letter','event-items',0,NULL,'Allows access to Seabreak path, Flower Paradise, and Shaymin.','Grants access to Flower Paradise and Shaymin.',0,1,NULL),(430,'lunar-wing','Lunar Wing','event-items',0,NULL,'Cures sailor’s son of nightmares in Canalave City.','Cures the sailor’s son of his nightmares; no reward, only a side effect of seeing Cresselia.',0,1,NULL),(431,'member-card','Member Card','event-items',0,NULL,'Allows access to Newmoon Island and Darkrai.','Provides access to Newmoon Island and Darkrai.',0,1,NULL),(432,'azure-flute','Azure Flute','event-items',0,NULL,'Allows entry into the Hall of Origin. Unreleased.',NULL,0,1,NULL),(433,'ss-ticket','S.S. Ticket','plot-advancement',0,NULL,'Ticket for a ship. (RSE: S.S. Tidal LF: S.S. Anne HG: S.S. Aqua)','Allows passage on a ferry. The same item is used for different ferries between different games.',0,1,NULL),(434,'contest-pass','Contest Pass','gameplay',0,NULL,'Allows participation in Pokémon Contests.','Allows the trainer to enter Contests.',0,1,NULL),(435,'magma-stone','Magma Stone','plot-advancement',0,NULL,'Magma is sealed inside.','Causes Heatran to appear at Reversal Mountain. Unused prior to Black and White 2.',0,1,NULL),(436,'parcel','Parcel','plot-advancement',0,NULL,'Given to the trainer’s rival in Jubilife City. Contains Town Maps.','Given to the trainer’s rival in Jubilife City. Contains two Town Maps, one of which is given to the trainer upon delivery.',0,1,NULL),(437,'coupon-1','Coupon 1','plot-advancement',0,NULL,'The first of three tickets used to obtain a Pokétch.','One of three coupons needed to receive a Pokétch.',0,1,NULL),(438,'coupon-2','Coupon 2','plot-advancement',0,NULL,'The second of three tickets used to obtain a Pokétch.','One of three coupons needed to receive a Pokétch.',0,1,NULL),(439,'coupon-3','Coupon 3','plot-advancement',0,NULL,'The last of three tickets used to obtain a Pokétch.','One of three coupons needed to receive a Pokétch.',0,1,NULL),(440,'storage-key','Storage Key','plot-advancement',0,NULL,'Grants access to the Team Galactic warehouse in Veilstone City.','Grants access to the Team Galactic warehouse in Veilstone City.',0,1,NULL),(441,'secret-potion','Secret Potion','plot-advancement',0,NULL,'Used to heal the Ampharos at the top of Olivine Lighthouse.','Required to cure the Psyducks blocking Route 210 of their chronic headaches.',0,1,NULL),(442,'griseous-orb','Griseous Orb','species-specific',0,60,'Boosts the damage from Giratina’s Dragon-type and Ghost-type moves by 20%, and transforms it into Origin Forme.','Held by Giratina : Holder’s Dragon and Ghost moves have 1.2× their base power. Holder is in Origin Forme. This item cannot be held by any Pokémon but Giratina. When you enter the Union Room or connect to Wi-Fi, this item returns to your bag.',1,0,'Not in PC. Not present in the Champions Database held items list.'),(443,'vs-recorder','Vs. Recorder','gameplay',0,NULL,'Records wireless, Wi-Fi, or Battle Frontier battles, and stores points.','Optionally records wireless, Wi-Fi, and Battle Frontier battles. Tracks Battle Points earned in the Battle Frontier, and stores commemorative prints.',0,1,NULL),(444,'gracidea','Gracidea','event-items',0,NULL,'Changes an unfrozen Shaymin to Sky Forme in the day.','Used by trainer on a Shaymin : Changes the target Shaymin from Land Forme to Sky Forme. This item cannot be used on a frozen Shaymin or at night. Sky Forme Shaymin will revert to Land Forme overnight, when frozen, and upon entering a link battle. This item must be used again to change it back.',0,1,NULL),(445,'secret-key','Secret Key','event-items',0,NULL,'Gen IV: The key to Rotom’s appliance room. Gen III: The key to Cinnabar Gym.','Used by trainer in the Galactic Eterna Building, on the ground floor, to the left of the TV : Unlocks the secret Rotom room, in which there are five appliances which can change Rotom’s form.',0,1,NULL),(446,'apricorn-box','Apricorn Box','gameplay',0,NULL,'Holds Apricorns.','Stores Apricorns.',0,1,NULL),(447,'berry-pots','Berry Pots','gameplay',0,NULL,'Allows portable berry growing.','Contains four portable pots of soil suitable for growing berries.',0,1,NULL),(448,'squirt-bottle','Squirt Bottle','plot-advancement',0,NULL,'Use on Sudowoodo blocking the path on Route 36. Also waters berries.','Required to water berries within the Berry Pots. Required to battle the Sudowoodo on Route 36. This item cannot be directly used from the bag.',0,1,NULL),(449,'lure-ball','Lure Ball','apricorn-balls',0,NULL,'3× effectiveness while fishing. Made from Blu Apricorn.','Used by trainer in battle : Attempts to catch a wild Pokémon. If used in a trainer battle, nothing happens and the ball is lost. If the wild Pokémon was encountered by fishing, the wild Pokémon’s catch rate is 3× normal.',0,1,NULL),(450,'level-ball','Level Ball','apricorn-balls',0,NULL,'Success rate based off of fraction target Pokémon is of user’s Pokémon. Made from Red Apricorn.','Used by trainer in battle : Attempts to catch a wild Pokémon. If used in a trainer battle, nothing happens and the ball is lost. If the trainer’s Pokémon’s level is higher than: * four times the wild Pokémon’s, the wild Pokémon’s catch rate is 8× normal. * than twice the wild Pokémon’s, the wild Pokémon’s catch rate is 4× normal. * the wild Pokémon’s, the wild Pokémon’s catch rate is 2× normal.',0,1,NULL),(451,'moon-ball','Moon Ball','apricorn-balls',0,NULL,'4× effectiveness on familes of Pokémon with a Moon Stone evolution. Made from Ylw Apricorn.','Used by trainer in battle : Attempts to catch a wild Pokémon. If used in a trainer battle, nothing happens and the ball is lost. If the wild Pokémon is a Clefairy, Nidoran♂, Nidoran♀, Jigglypuff, Skitty, or any evolution thereof, the wild Pokémon has 4× its catch rate.',0,1,NULL),(452,'heavy-ball','Heavy Ball','apricorn-balls',0,NULL,'Has flat bonus or penalty to catch rate depending on weight class of target. Made from Blk Apricorn.','Used by a trainer in battle : Attempts to catch a wild Pokémon. If used in a trainer battle, nothing happens and the ball is lost. If the wild Pokémon weighs: * 409.6 kg (903.0 lb) or more, its catch rate is 40 more than normal. * 307.2 kg (677.3 lb) or more, its catch rate is 30 more than normal. * 204.8 kg (451.5 lb) or more, its catch rate is 20 more than normal. * less than 204.8 kg (451.5 lb), its catch rate is 20 less than normal.',0,1,NULL),(453,'fast-ball','Fast Ball','apricorn-balls',0,NULL,'4× effectiveness on Pokémon with 100 or greater base speed. (Gen II: Roaming or Fleeing Pokémon). Made from Wht Apricorn.','Used by a trainer in battle : Attempts to catch a wild Pokémon. If used in a trainer battle, nothing happens and the ball is lost. : If the wild Pokémon’s base speed is 100 or more, its catch rate is 4× normal.',0,1,NULL),(454,'friend-ball','Friend Ball','apricorn-balls',0,NULL,'Caught Pokémon start with 200 happiness. Made from Grn Apricorn.','Used by a trainer in battle : Attempts to catch a wild Pokémon. If used in a trainer battle, nothing happens and the ball is lost. If caught, the wild Pokémon’s happiness starts at 200.',0,1,NULL),(455,'love-ball','Love Ball','apricorn-balls',0,NULL,'8× effectiveness on opposite sex, same species targets of the Active Pokémon. Made from Pnk Apricorn.','Used by a trainer in battle : Attempts to catch a wild Pokémon. If used in a trainer battle, nothing happens and the ball is lost. If the trainer’s Pokémon and wild Pokémon are of the same species but opposite genders, the wild Pokémon’s catch rate is 8× normal.',0,1,NULL),(456,'park-ball','Park Ball','standard-balls',0,NULL,'Catches Pokémon in the Pal Park every time.','Used by a trainer in battle : Catches a wild Pokémon. This item can only be used in Pal Park.',0,1,NULL),(457,'sport-ball','Sport Ball','standard-balls',300,NULL,'Tries to catch a Pokémon in the Bug-Catching contest in National Park. (Gen II: Park Ball)','Used by a trainer in battle : Attempts to catch a wild Pokémon. The wild Pokémon’s catch rate is 1.5× normal.',0,1,NULL),(458,'red-apricorn','Red Apricorn','apricorn-box',200,10,'Used to make a Level Ball.','May be given to Kurt in Azalea Town to produce a Level Ball.',0,1,NULL),(459,'blue-apricorn','Blue Apricorn','apricorn-box',200,10,'Used to make a Lure Ball.','May be given to Kurt in Azalea Town to produce a Lure Ball.',0,1,NULL),(460,'yellow-apricorn','Yellow Apricorn','apricorn-box',200,10,'Used to make a Moon Ball.','May be given to Kurt in Azalea Town to produce a Moon Ball.',0,1,NULL),(461,'green-apricorn','Green Apricorn','apricorn-box',200,10,'Used to make a Friend Ball.','May be given to Kurt in Azalea Town to produce a Friend Ball.',0,1,NULL),(462,'pink-apricorn','Pink Apricorn','apricorn-box',200,10,'Used to make a Love Ball.','May be given to Kurt in Azalea Town to produce a Love Ball.',0,1,NULL),(463,'white-apricorn','White Apricorn','apricorn-box',200,10,'Used to make a Fast Ball.','May be given to Kurt in Azalea Town to produce a Fast Ball.',0,1,NULL),(464,'black-apricorn','Black Apricorn','apricorn-box',200,10,'Used to make a Heavy Ball.','May be given to Kurt in Azalea Town to produce a Heavy Ball.',0,1,NULL),(465,'dowsing-machine','Dowsing Machine','gameplay',0,NULL,'Use to find hidden items on the field. AKA Itemfinder.','Used by trainer outside of battle : Searches for hidden items.',0,1,NULL),(466,'rage-candy-bar','Rage Candy Bar','gameplay',350,30,'HS: Traded for TM64. Gen II & Gen V: Acts as a Potion.','May be traded for a TM64 in the vertical Underground Path.',0,1,NULL),(467,'red-orb','Red Orb','plot-advancement',0,NULL,'Summons Groudon to the Embedded Tower.','Causes Groudon to appear in the Embedded Tower.',0,1,NULL),(468,'blue-orb','Blue Orb','plot-advancement',0,NULL,'Summons Kyogre to the Embedded Tower.','Causes Kyogre to appear in the Embedded Tower.',0,1,NULL),(469,'jade-orb','Jade Orb','plot-advancement',0,NULL,'Summons Rayquaza to the Embedded Tower.','Causes Rayquaza to appear in the Embedded Tower.',0,1,NULL),(470,'enigma-stone','Enigma Stone','event-items',0,NULL,'S: Summons Latias H: Summons Latios.','When taken to the Pewter City museum, causes Latias or Latios to attack the trainer. The Pokémon to appear will be whicher can’t be encountered roaming in the wild.',0,1,NULL),(471,'unown-report','Unown Report','gameplay',0,NULL,'Keeps track of Unown types caught.','Lists which Unown forms the trainer has caught.',0,1,NULL),(472,'blue-card','Blue Card','gameplay',0,NULL,'Keeps track of points from Buena’s show.','Allows the trainer to answer the daily question on Buena’s radio show. Records the points earned for correct answers.',0,1,NULL),(473,'slowpoke-tail','Slowpoke Tail','unused',0,NULL,'A tasty tail that sells for a high price.','Does nothing.',0,1,NULL),(474,'clear-bell','Clear Bell','plot-advancement',0,NULL,'HS: Allows Kimono-girls to summon Ho-oh. C: Summons Suicune to the Tin Tower.','May be given to the Kimono Girls to summon Ho-Oh to the top of the Bell Tower.',0,1,NULL),(475,'card-key','Card Key','plot-advancement',0,NULL,'HS: Opens doors in the Radio Tower. Gen III: Unlocks Silph Co Doors.','Used by trainer outside of battle : Opens doors in the Goldenrod City Radio Tower.',0,1,NULL),(476,'basement-key','Basement Key','plot-advancement',0,NULL,'HS: Key to the tunnel under Goldenrod City. Gen III: Key to New Mauville.','Used by trainer outside of battle : Opens the door to the basement tunnel under Goldenrod City.',0,1,NULL),(477,'red-scale','Red Scale','plot-advancement',0,NULL,'Trade to Mr. Pokémon for an Exp. Share.','May be traded to Mr. Pokémon for an Exp. Share.',0,1,NULL),(478,'lost-item','Lost Item','plot-advancement',0,NULL,'A Poké Doll lost by the Copycat who lives in Saffron City. Trade for a Pass.','May be traded to the Copycat for a Pass.',0,1,NULL),(479,'pass','Pass','plot-advancement',0,NULL,'Grants access to ride the Magnet Train between Goldenrod City and Saffron City.','Allows the trainer to ride the Magnet Train between Goldenrod City and Saffron City.',0,1,NULL),(480,'machine-part','Machine Part','plot-advancement',0,NULL,'Must be replaced in the Power Plant to power the Magnet Train.','Must be replaced in the Kanto Power Plant to power the Magnet Train.',0,1,NULL),(481,'silver-wing','Silver Wing','plot-advancement',0,NULL,'Summons Lugia to the Whirl Islands.','Causes Lugia to appear in the Whirl Islands.',0,1,NULL),(482,'rainbow-wing','Rainbow Wing','plot-advancement',0,NULL,'Summons Ho-Oh at the top of the Bell Tower.','Causes Ho-Oh to appear at the top of Bell Tower.',0,1,NULL),(483,'mystery-egg','Mystery Egg','plot-advancement',0,NULL,'Deliver to Professor Elm.','Must be obtained to trigger the break-in at Professor Elm’s lab, the first rival battle, and access to Route 31.',0,1,NULL),(484,'gb-sounds','GB Sounds','gameplay',0,NULL,'Use to listen to GameBoy era audio.','Used by trainer outside of battle : Changes the background music to the equivalent 8-bit music.',0,1,NULL),(485,'tidal-bell','Tidal Bell','plot-advancement',0,NULL,'Allows Kimono-girls to summon Lugia.','May be given to the Kimono Girls to summon Lugia to the top of the Bell Tower.',0,1,NULL),(486,